                     <origDate notBefore="1770" notAfter="1849">Late 18th/first half of
                       the 19th century</origDate>.
                       The names of the original commissioners or owners have been erased from the supplication
                       formulas. Names of other individuals have been written instead, such as
                       <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13844ZawgaMikael">Zawga Mikāʾel</persName>,
                       his son <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13842WaldaWahed">Walda Wāḥǝd</persName>,
                          <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13843GabraWahed">Gabra Wāḥǝd</persName> and others (possibly belonging to
                          the same family). <ref target="#a1">Additional note 1</ref> seems to tell that
                          <persName role="donor" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13844ZawgaMikael">Zawga Mikāʾel</persName> donated the manuscript to
                          <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC7366DabraGiyorgis">Dabra Giyorgis</placeName> in the district <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC7365Gucari">Guč̣āri</placeName>.
                          </origin>
                        <provenance>The manuscript was acquired by
                          <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1071dAbbadi">Antoine d'Abbadie</persName>
                          sometime between <date>1840</date> and <date>1848</date>.
                        </provenance>
                      <acquisition>The manuscript entered <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0303BNF">the Bibliothèque nationale</placeName> in
                        <date>1902</date>.
                  </acquisition>
